extract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cross, to traverse"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ford"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to swim (something)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pass over"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to interpret","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"يَا أَيُّهَا ٱلْمَلَأُ أَفْتُونِي فِي رُؤْيَايَ إِنْ كُنْتُمْ لِلرُّؤْيَا تَعْبُرُونَ","english":"O people give me your opinion about my vision if you can see through it!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَبَرَ (ʕabara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"across"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to get across; to make cross, to cause to pass over, to convey across","tags":["ditransitive","literally","obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to get across; to express, to put into terms","tags":["ditransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to interpret","tags":["transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ʕabar-. Compare Hebrew עָבַר (ʿāḇar, “to cross”), Old South Arabian 𐩲𐩨𐩧 (ʿbr, “to transgress”), Akkadian 𒁄 (ebēru, “to cross”).\n\nAdverbial accusative of عَبْر (ʕabr, “crossing”). Compare Old South Arabian 𐩲𐩨𐩧 (ʿbr, “towards”).\n\nCausative of the preceding verb عَبَرَ (ʕabara) and in the meanings of explaining, interpreting, expressing a semantic loan from Middle Persian [Book Pahlavi needed] (wtltn' /⁠widārdan⁠/, “to cause to pass”) = Early New Persian گذاردن (guḏārdan, “to cause to pass; to clean, to purge; to put, to place”), [Book Pahlavi needed] (wcʾltn' /⁠wizārdan⁠/, “to separate; to explain, to interpret, to express”) = گزاردن (guzārdan /gozârdan, “to cause to pass; to draw the outline of a picture; to express”)."},"ipa":null}